## Phase 8: Harden lifecycle and failure recovery

- [x] Run mount reset before and after every Busted example.
- [x] Preserve strict LIFO cleanup for component, host screen, pointer state,
  pause state, lifecycle callbacks, and render interception.
- [x] Ensure assertion failures, command errors, render errors, timeouts,
  external lease expiry, and explicit abort all drain mount resources.
- [x] Make cleanup idempotent after explicit unmount.
- [x] Report cleanup failures without hiding the originating test failure.
- [x] Retain bounded mount-tree and screen captures for failed interactions.
- [x] Confirm that a failed example cannot leak its current mount or subjects
  into the following example.

Exit evidence:

- [x] Resilience unit tests cover every terminal path.
- [x] Live abort and timeout reports have `cleanup_confirmed=true` and leave no
  DwarfSpec-owned screen active.

Phase 8 evidence (2026-07-20):

- DwarfSpec installs root Busted hooks that call the run-owned reset with
  distinct `before example` and `after example` reasons. Reset drains the
  shared registry in strict LIFO order, waits one live frame even after a
  cleanup action fails, and remains idempotent after explicit unmount and
  repeated reset. Existing adapter contracts plus the
  failed-overlay live proof cover component ownership, overlay disable and
  state restoration, host dismissal and pause restoration, pointer cleanup,
  render interception restoration, and complete-screen resize restoration.
- Terminal reports now include `mount_cleanup_state` with an explicit
  verification result, active and tracked owned-screen counts, live subject
  count, and virtual-pointer state. Cleanup confirmation requires no current
  mount, no active owned screen, no live subject ownership, no pointer patch,
  no pending cleanup, coroutine, scheduler, wait, or timer, and no cleanup
  failure anywhere earlier in the run.
- Cleanup failures retained from per-example hooks make
  `cleanup_confirmed=false`. Run `lifecycle-combined-failure-final` records the
  original Luassert failure and the distinct `after_each` cleanup error as two
  details without replacing either one; its lifecycle probe still verifies
  zero active screens, subjects, and pointer patches.
- Mount-tree diagnostics are bounded to depth 8 and 128 nodes by default and
  carry explicit truncation metadata. Failed-interaction screen evidence
  remains bounded to 16 by 8 cells. Unit tests cover both depth and node limits,
  and live command/render failures retain the bounded tree and screen data
  across cleanup.
- Focused Busted contracts pass 5 cleanup-registry, 10 automation-host, 14
  mount-context, 2 diagnostics, 14 external-runner, 5 public mount-command,
  and 3 adapter tests. Together they cover strict LIFO continuation,
  before/after reset, cleanup-failure history, false-confirmation rejection,
  assertion/error propagation, render failure, command failure, internal and
  external timeout, abort, lease expiry, stale generation, second-mount
  rejection, and idempotent unmount cleanup.
- `tools/Run-UnitTests.ps1` passes 125 tests with no failures, errors, or
  pending tests. `tools/Check-Lua.ps1` passes Lua 5.4.6 syntax and formatting
  checks for 88 Lua files; `luarocks lint dwarfspec-0.1.0-1.rockspec` and
  `git diff --check` pass.
- Product-independent failure runs in embedded Lua 5.3 intentionally finish
  non-passing while proving recovery: `lifecycle-assertion-final` records one
  expected assertion failure followed by one successful leak check;
  `lifecycle-command-timeout-final` records the expected command error and
  in-coroutine timeout followed by two successful leak checks; and
  `lifecycle-overlay-final` records one expected assertion failure followed by
  a successful lifecycle-order check. All three record
  `cleanup_confirmed=true`, lifecycle verification true, zero active screens,
  zero subjects, and no pointer patch.
- External wall-clock timeout report `lifecycle-timeout-final` and explicit
  abort report `lifecycle-explicit-abort-final` both finish `state=aborted`,
  `cleanup_confirmed=true`, lifecycle verification true, zero active owned
  screens, zero subjects, and no pointer patch. Direct native run
  `lifecycle-lease-expiry-final` aborts after its 218 ms unpolled lease and
  reports the same cleanup proof with reason `status lease expired after 218
  ms`.
- The complete product-independent live suite passes 19 tests with no
  failures or errors in embedded Lua 5.3. Report `lifecycle-final-suite`
  records `cleanup_confirmed=true`, `cleanup_reason="suite completion"`,
  lifecycle verification true, zero active screens, zero subjects, and no
  pointer patch.

## Phase 9: Separate component and overlay-integration coverage

- [x] Migrate overlay behavior tests to `ds.mount(OverlayWidget, options)`.
- [x] Retain a minimal integration test for real `OVERLAY_WIDGETS` discovery,
  registration, rescan, enablement, positioning, focus filtering, and cleanup.
- [x] Keep any run-owned script staging helper internal unless consumers have a
  demonstrated need to author registration integration tests.
- [x] Ensure an integration helper cannot overwrite product scripts or persist
  configuration changes.
- [x] Name and document integration tests distinctly from component tests.

Exit evidence:

- [x] Overlay component behavior is proven without copying files into
  `hack/scripts/gui`.
- [x] The smaller integration suite proves the DFHack overlay boundary and
  restores every modified external artifact.

Phase 9 evidence (2026-07-20):

- Product-independent overlay behavior remains in
  `tests/automation/specs/overlay_widget_mount_live_spec.lua`. Both its class
  and existing-instance examples use `ds.mount`, implicit `ds.get` subjects,
  interaction, inspection, synchronization, unmount, and automatic cleanup.
  Dedicated run `phase9-overlay-component` passes both examples with
  `cleanup_confirmed=true`, zero active owned screens, zero subjects, and no
  pointer patch. It does not stage or discover a script.
- The obsolete command-project `overlay_spec.ds.lua` and its two runner-probe
  fixture files were removed. The remaining real boundary is explicitly named
  `overlay_registration_integration_spec.lua`; its filename does not match the
  normal `*_live_spec.lua` component glob and it is selected separately.
- The registration suite uses an internal function stored on the active run,
  not another public mount operation. The pre-existing
  `ds.stage_overlay_fixture` compatibility entry delegates to the hardened
  implementation only while DwarfUI's demonstrated registration-oriented
  caller awaits the consumer migration below; the new DwarfSpec component and
  integration specs do not depend on that public fixture protocol.
- Registration staging accepts only a project-relative imported definition,
  derives a run-unique `dwarfspec_*` destination, refuses any existing target,
  and registers cleanup before writing or rescanning. Cleanup disables every
  discovered staged widget, refuses to delete changed script contents,
  restores the prior `dfhack-config/overlay.json` artifact exactly (including
  restoring absence), removes the unchanged run-owned script, rescans, and
  verifies that its database registrations are gone. Cleanup attempts every
  restoration step and aggregates failures instead of abandoning later work.
- Five focused unit contracts prove exact script/config/registration cleanup,
  collision refusal, partial-rescan rollback, preservation of a changed staged
  path, and removal of a configuration file created during a run. The complete
  unit suite passes 127 tests with no failures, errors, or pending tests;
  `tools/Check-Lua.ps1` passes Lua 5.4.6 syntax and formatting checks for 87
  files; and `luarocks lint dwarfspec-0.1.0-1.rockspec` passes.
- Dedicated embedded-Lua-5.3 run `phase9-overlay-registration-final` passes two
  integration examples. The first proves real `OVERLAY_WIDGETS` discovery and
  database registration, default-disabled state, framework enable callbacks,
  persisted position `{x=7,y=-4}` and matching frame anchors, a broad
  `dwarfmode` update, and rejection of a deliberately nonmatching focus
  string. The following example proves both disable callbacks ran, the staged
  script is absent, both database entries are absent, and the configuration
  bytes equal their pre-run snapshot. Its terminal report records
  `cleanup_confirmed=true` and a verified empty mount lifecycle.
- An independent filesystem comparison measured overlay configuration SHA-256
  `41A90CBF90ABB9CDECD1468AFC1734DB924310F9F50B85B4B4B9BC6F243B9F15`
  both before and after the registration run; the run-specific staged path was
  absent before and after. The complete normal live matrix subsequently passes
  19 examples in `phase9-full-live-final` with no failures or errors,
  `cleanup_confirmed=true`, zero active screens, zero subjects, and no pointer
  patch. An earlier matrix attempt encountered the existing documented focus
  precondition as `dwarfmode/Building/Placement`; after the game returned to
  `dwarfmode/Default`, the unchanged suite passed.

## Phase 10: Remove the fixture protocol and migrate consumers

- [x] Replace DwarfSpec's `show_fixture` self-tests with direct component
  mounts.
- [x] Replace `stage_overlay_fixture` behavior tests with overlay component
  mounts, retaining only the integration coverage identified above.
- [x] Migrate DwarfUI live specs to direct mounts and fluent subjects.
- [x] Convert reusable fixture modules into ordinary constructors, data
  builders, or product-independent test-support helpers.
- [x] Remove manual `render_generation` fields and `on_automation_shown` hooks
  from consumer test components.
- [x] Remove or formally deprecate `ds.show_fixture`, `ds.dismiss(screen)`, and
  `ds.stage_overlay_fixture` after all in-repository consumers migrate.
- [x] Remove fixture-loader and overlay-fixture modules that have no remaining
  integration responsibility.
- [x] Confirm the configurable `*.ds.lua` discovery contract continues to
  exclude conventional `*.fixture.lua` and support files by default.

Exit evidence:

- [x] Repository search finds no consumer-authored `render_generation`, no
  normal interaction that passes a root or screen, and no obsolete fixture API
  usage.
- [x] DwarfSpec and DwarfUI unit and live suites pass against the same installed
  rock artifact.

Phase 10 evidence (2026-07-20):

- DwarfSpec's interaction, failure, and minimal-project live specs now declare
  their components directly and use `ds.mount`, implicit `ds.get` lookup, and
  fluent subjects. The former fixture loader, overlay-fixture staging module,
  three screen fixtures, and registration-definition fixture were removed.
  The retained `*.fixture.lua` and support-file sentinels prove default
  discovery exclusion without defining a DwarfSpec fixture protocol.
- The public `show_fixture`, `dismiss`, and `stage_overlay_fixture` operations
  are absent. Real registration tests use the distinctly named
  `stage_overlay_registration` integration helper and remain outside the
  normal component-test glob. The packed manifest includes
  `overlay_registration.lua`, `mount_context.lua`, and `ds.lua`, and contains
  neither `fixture_loader.lua` nor `overlay_fixture.lua`.
- DwarfUI's normal tooltip and tooltip-overlay specs mount an inline complete
  screen and an inline overlay component directly. They use fluent subjects
  and contain no automation render counter or hook. Its separately selected
  registration integration uses an ordinary support definition and exercises
  real discovery, enablement, focus eligibility, disablement, and reversible
  cleanup.
- Repository-wide active-code searches in both repositories find no obsolete
  fixture API call, consumer-authored `render_generation`,
  `on_automation_shown`, two-argument `ds.get`, or normal raw-target
  interaction. Remaining `render_generation` matches are negative assertions
  that prove components are not required to implement it; legacy names occur
  only in negative export/package assertions and historical planning evidence.
- The complete DwarfSpec unit suite passes 128 tests with no failures, errors,
  or pending tests. `tools/Check-Lua.ps1` passes Lua 5.4.6 syntax and formatting
  checks for 82 files; `luarocks lint dwarfspec-0.1.0-1.rockspec` and
  `git diff --check` pass. DwarfUI's complete unit suite passes 69 tests with no
  failures, errors, or pending tests, its production syntax gate passes all 5
  files with Lua 5.4.6, and the four migrated live/support files pass explicit
  `luac -p` parsing.
- Binary rock `dwarfspec-0.1.0-1.win32-x86_64.rock`, SHA-256
  `B5025DBE398515D4BACB4CEB3AE23D6AF4ACF4843E7089740D0E2C811393D98D`,
  was built and force-installed into the isolated `.package-phase10` tree.
  The installed bootstrap hash exactly matches the source bootstrap. Every
  live run below used that tree's `bin/dwarfspec.bat`, with the external Lua
  5.4 toolchain handing pure Lua to DFHack's embedded Lua 5.3 runtime.
- Product-independent run `phase10-artifact-dwarfspec-constructor-final`
  passes all 19 examples, covering widget, overlay-widget, and complete-screen
  classes and instances. Run `phase10-artifact-registration-final` separately
  passes both real overlay-registration examples. Both report
  `cleanup_confirmed=true`, lifecycle verification true, and zero active
