Phase 11 evidence (2026-07-21):

- `README.md` and `docs/writing-tests.md` now lead with `ds.mount(component,
  options)`, implicit `ds.get(view_id)`, and fluent subjects. The writing guide
  contains explicit ordinary-widget, overlay-widget, and complete-screen
  examples and shows both constructor and existing-instance input forms. It
  distinguishes isolated overlay component behavior from the distinctly
  named and separately selected real registration integration.
- `docs/architecture.md` assigns the host screen, mount identity, view index,
  weak subject ownership, render instrumentation and tracking, diagnostics,
  adapters, synchronization, and LIFO cleanup to DwarfSpec. It documents the
  ordinary-widget, overlay lifecycle, and direct complete-screen adapter
  boundaries and states that render instrumentation remains private to
  DwarfSpec without altering component classes.
- `docs/command-line.md` presents only the current mount and registration
  commands. `CHANGELOG.md` describes the initial unreleased API without a
  migration, changed, or removed section. Installation, configuration,
  contributing, and release guidance use the same current model and toolchain
  contract.
- The complete DwarfSpec unit suite passes 129 tests with no failures, errors,
  or pending tests. Local Lua 5.4.6 parses and formatting-checks all 82 Lua
  files; a single compile-only DFHack invocation parses the same 82 files with
  embedded Lua 5.3. `git diff --check` passes. DwarfUI's complete unit suite
  passes 69 tests, its Lua 5.4.6 production syntax gate passes all 5 files, and
  its four migrated live/support files pass explicit `luac -p` parsing.
- The committed VS Code `Publish` task runs `tools/Publish.ps1`, which creates
  a temporary correctly versioned rockspec, passes `luarocks lint`, and packs
  `dist/dwarfspec-0.1.0-1.all.rock`. SHA-256
  `9C18B61E62789AC75C5B2169D1CE3C88783BA9FDF7AEC35100211A7B4DB70E99`
  identifies the exact release artifact used below. Its 39-entry manifest
  contains the paired launchers, `ds`, mount-context, component-adapter, and
  registration modules and contains no native library.
- A previously absent `.package-release` tree received the declared pinned
  LuaRocks dependencies and that exact `.all.rock`. The installed
  `dwarfspec version` command reports `DwarfSpec 0.1.0`; installed
  `dwarfspec.ds` and `dwarfspec.component` module smoke checks pass. LuaRocks
  lists DwarfSpec 0.1.0-1, Busted 2.3.0-1, and LuaSystem 0.3.0-2 in that tree.
- Installed-artifact run `release-final-components-v3` passes all 19
  product-independent examples, covering ordinary widgets, overlay widgets,
  and complete screens as both constructors and existing instances through
  the same author-facing mount and subject commands. Separately selected run
